title.narrative: Control and Prevention of Tuberculosis (CAP-TB) in the Mekong Region

description.narrative: (USAID Regional Development Mission-Asia (RDM/A)): .USAID RDMA's CAP-TB activity will continue to strengthen national and community-based efforts to combat multi-drug resistant tuberculosis (MDR-TB) in the Mekong region. Using FY 2016 funds, the program will provide technical assistance to refine and implement comprehensive models for community-based interventions to better control the disease as well as to strengthen MDR-TB programs and services. The program's overall approach is founded upon patient-centered, community-driven implementation to enable faster diagnosis, higher treatment success rates, and more effective prevention of MDR-TB. In Thailand and China, RDMA will continue to strengthen the linkage between TB control systems and treatment facilities, as well as support the decentralization of TB expertise to provincial levels. .
